@*
===============================================================================
 File        : AppHost.razor
 Author      : Michael
 Version     : 4.3.0
 Created     : 2026-03-23
 Updated     : 2026-04-06
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Purpose     : Root Blazor component for the MAUI BlazorWebView.

               Hosts the global splash screen, router, and error boundary.
               Ensures deterministic application startup and safe transition
               from branded loading experience to interactive UI.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Changes     :
   - 1.0.0  2026-03-23  Initial implementation.
   - 2.0.0  2026-03-24  Removed BaseLayoutV2 wrapper (Routes was swallowed).
   - 2.1.0  2026-03-24  Added @using AbsenceApp.Client for <Routes /> resolution.
   - 3.0.0  2026-03-27  Section A fix: wrapped <Routes /> with
                        GlobalErrorBoundaryV2 so all unhandled exceptions are
                        caught globally, logged, and shown as a styled fallback.
   - 4.0.0  2026-03-28  Phase 4 fix: added SplashScreenV2 shown for 1 500 ms
                        on first load before the router is revealed. Restores
                        the branded loading experience that was missing in V2.
   - 4.1.0  2026-04-05  Injected EntitlementsService at the Blazor root so
                        layouts and pages can evaluate permissions.
   - 4.2.0  2026-04-06  Option A: removed EntitlementsService injection.
                        Feature permission checks now flow through the API.
   - 4.3.0  2026-04-06  MAUI fix: splash screen is now always rendered and
                        visibility-controlled to prevent native input capture
                        blocking the application after initial load.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Notes       :
   - MAUI BlazorWebView can retain native views after conditional removal.
   - SplashScreenV2 must remain mounted and release pointer events explicitly.
===============================================================================
*@
@using AbsenceApp.Client
@using AbsenceApp.Client.Framework.Layouts
@using AbsenceApp.Client.Services

@* ===========================================================================
   Section: SPLASH SCREEN
   Always rendered to avoid MAUI native view retention.
   Visibility and pointer interaction are controlled internally.
   ========================================================================== *@
<SplashScreenV2 Visible="_showSplash" />

@* ===========================================================================
   Section: GLOBAL ERROR BOUNDARY & ROUTER
   Always rendered so the application remains interactive regardless of
   splash screen state.
   ========================================================================== *@
<GlobalErrorBoundaryV2>
    <Routes />
</GlobalErrorBoundaryV2>

@code {
    private bool _showSplash = true;

    protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
    {
        if (firstRender)
        {
            await Task.Delay(1500);
            _showSplash = false;
            StateHasChanged();
        }
    }
}
